HEADWORD: Sulphuration
<hw>Sul`phu*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sulfuration</ets>, L. <ets>sulphuratio</ets>,
<ets>sulfuratio</ets>, a vein of sulphur.]</ety> <def>The act or process
of combining or impregnating with sulphur or its compounds; also, the
state of being so combined or impregnated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

